      <bioghist id="aspace_0c1c67902d7f7e88da7f18ebae9acc49">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Stephen Herbert Hymer was born in Montreal, Quebec, Canada in 1934. He received a B.A. from McGill University in 1955 and a Ph.D. from MIT in 1960. Hymer was an assistant professor at MIT from 1962-1963, an assistant professor of economics at Yale University from 1963-1970, and a professor of economics at the New School for Social Research from 1970-1974. In addition to his work on the multinational corporation, Hymer was interested in economic development, especially in the context of Africa. He died in 1974.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_3a2d3fd8cedae608117b6048c45f9c28">
